Step by Step to "Reproduce" the works in this Nature paper:
https://www.nature.com/articles/s44386-025-00007-4?utm_source=rct_congratemailt&utm_medium=email&utm_campaign=oa_20250402&utm_content=10.1038/s44386-025-00007-4

ðŸ’« Harnessing DNA-Encoded Libraries and Machine Learning for Efficient Hit Drug Discovery: A Benchmark Study Across DELâ€‰+â€‰ML Combinations

ðŸ§ª Study Focus: Combining DEL and ML for Drug Discovery

The goal of this study was to evaluate how well DNA-Encoded Libraries (DELs) and Machine Learning (ML) models work together to discover potential drug candidates, also known as â€œhits.â€ Specifically, they wanted to know which combinations of DELs and ML models are most effective for predicting molecules that bind to a drug target.

ðŸ‘‰ Part 1: Installation

conda env create --name del-ml-gpu -f ./docs/environment_gpu.yml

conda activate del-ml-gpu

Pre-requisites:

Linux (Tested on Ubuntu 22.04)

NVIDIA GPU (Tested on NVIDIA RTX A6000 with cuda version 12.1)

Python (3.10)

Tensorflow (2.14)

chemprop (1.6.1)

RDkit (2023.9.2)

Pytorch (2.1.1)

ðŸ‘‰ Part 2: Test codes

ðŸ’« Step 1: Feature extraction

python feature_extractor.py --input_file ./example/compound.csv --save_path ./example/ --experiment compound_feature

ðŸ’«  Results of the test:

~/Documents/Truong/DEL-ML-Refactor/example$ ls -l

-> Output file: compound_feature.h5

ðŸ’« Step 2: Binder/Non-binder Prediction

1. Multi-layer perceptron (MLP)

ðŸ’« python prediction.py --input_file ./example/compound_feature.h5 --save_path ./example/ --experiment compound_pred_mlp --checkpoint ./data/HitGen/models/CK1a/MLP.keras

ðŸ’« python prediction.py --input_file ./example/compound_feature.h5 --save_path ./example/ --experiment compound_pred_mlp --checkpoint ./data/HitGen/models/CK1a/MLP.keras --use_gpu

-> Output file: compound_pred_mlp.csv

2. Graph neural network (GNN)

ðŸ’« chemprop_predict --smiles_columns SMILES --test_path ./example/compound.csv --checkpoint_path data/HitGen/models/CK1a/chemprop.pt --preds_path ./example/compound_prediction_chemprop.csv

